               <head>Fath Nāma by ʿImrani</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070315">
                  <summary>Persian rendering of biblical stories.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="he" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="335v" />
                     <title xml:lang="en">Fath Nāma</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he">פתח נאמה</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A paraphrase of biblical stories from books of Joshua, Rut and Samuel
                           in Persian, in Hebrew characters.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="en">ʿImrani</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he">עמרני</persName>
                     </author>
                     <decoNote type="other">
                        <locus from="1r" to="90v" />Numerous inhabited and
                        decorated panels, in colours.
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="illustration">Unfinished full-page illustration, in pencil.<locus n="90v" />
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="illustration">6 miniatures, in colours: f. 15r: Joshua and the
                        priests are carrying the ark across the Jordan river; f. 31v: f. 31v: Seven
                        priests blow the shofar before the walls of Jericho; f. 32r: Joshua, riding
                        a white horse, is fighting before the walls of Jericho; f. 50v: Joshua on
                        horseback, spear in hand, participates in the battle; f. 75r: Joshua, riding
                        a black horse, is entering into batlle to come to the aid of the Gibeonites;
                        f. 85r: Joshua, riding his black charger, and his followers defeat the host
                        of the king of Mekkedah and his allies.</decoNote>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
